The paper focuses on the application of augmented reality (AR) and virtual reality (VR) technologies in the context of exploratory data analysis (EDA), which involves human-computer interaction and visualization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses the hardware capabilities of AR and VR, which suggests cs.VR (Virtual Reality and Augmented Reality) as another likely category. The use of data projections and visualizations also suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) as possible categories. Finally, the paper discusses the potential security and privacy concerns of using AR and VR in data analysis, which suggests cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) as a less likely but still possible category.
